  "description": [
    "THE CHRONICLE THURSDAY AUGUST 22 1963 Infamous Power Play The socalled Gesell Report has been described by Rep Joe D Waggoner Jr DLa as in famous and comparable to the action of the evil Benjamin Butler or Thaddeous Stevens despised figures of Reconstruction days who used all the powers at their com mand to abuse and humiliate a prostrate South The report is the work of a sevenman committee known as The Presidents Committee on Equal Opportunity in the Armed Forces and named after Gerhard Gesell a Washington attorney and committee chairman Its a fantas tic series of proposals to compel communities and people near mili tary establishments to abandon the practice of segregation on penalty of being placed offlimits It even directs base commanders to brain wash intimidate boycott and ostracize people communities and business and civic groups unless they integrate and recommend promotions for the commanders who go about this business of ci vilian meddling with enthusiasm Comparing these and its many other recommendations to the evils of Butler and Stevens might even be an understatement because they are so vicious Were proud that Southern Sen ators and Representatives are de nouncing this report and its imple mentation"
  ],
